# TypeScript & React

From [docs/coding_standards.md](../../docs/coding_standards.md).

## Typing

- Avoid `any`; use precise types and guards
- Exported APIs must be explicitly typed
- Never swallow errors silently

## React / Next.js

- Server Components by default; `'use client'` only for interactivity
- Page clients: co-locate as `*PageClient.tsx` next to routes
- Routing: `next/link`, `next/navigation` — not raw `<a>` for internal nav (except middle-click patterns)
- Images: `next/image` with width/height

## Naming

- Components: `PascalCase.tsx`, props type `ComponentNameProps`
- Utilities: `kebab-case.ts` or `camelCase.ts`
- Hooks: `use*` in `src/hooks/`
- Handlers: `handle*` prefix
- Booleans: `is/has/should/can` prefix

## Styling

- Tailwind only — semantic tokens (`bg`, `surface`, `text`, `muted`, `poke.*`, `type.*`)
- No inline styles for color/spacing; no new CSS files

## Data fetching

- Components call typed functions in `src/lib/api.ts`, not raw `fetch`
- Use `requestManager` signals for cancellable requests
